methods.name: parse

parameters.name: text
parameters.description: The string to parse.

methods.description: Parses a string, returning a new Date object. The string should be similar to the string returned bt toString().

methods.name: UTC

parameters.name: year
parameters.description: The year expressed in four digits, for example, 2001.
parameters.longdesc: To indicate for a year from 1900 to 1999, you can specify a value from 0 to 99.

parameters.name: month
parameters.description: An integer value from 0 (Jan) to 11 (Dec).

parameters.name: day
parameters.description: An integer value from 1 to 31, If this argument is not supplied, its value is set to 0.

parameters.name: hours
parameters.description: An integer value from 0 (midnight) to 23 (11 PM). If this argument is not supplied, its value is set to 0.

parameters.name: min
parameters.description: An integer value from 0 to 59. If this argument is not supplied, its value is set to 0.

parameters.name: sec
parameters.description: An Integer value from 0 to 59. If this argument is not supplied, its value is set to 0.

parameters.name: ms
parameters.description: An integer value from 0 to 999. If this argument is not supplied, its value is set to 0.

methods.description: Returns the number of milliseconds between midnight January 1, 1970, UTC, and the specified time.

methods.name: Date

parameters.name: year
parameters.description: The year expressed in four digits.

parameters.name: month
parameters.description: An integer value from 0 (Jan) to 11 (Dec).

parameters.name: day
parameters.description: An integer value from 1 to 31, If this argument is not supplied, its value is set to 0.

parameters.name: hours
parameters.description: An integer value from 0 (midnight) to 23 (11 PM). If this argument is not supplied, its value is set to 0.

parameters.name: min
parameters.description: An integer value from 0 to 59. If this argument is not supplied, its value is set to 0.

parameters.name: sec
parameters.description: An Integer value from 0 to 59. If this argument is not supplied, its value is set to 0.

parameters.name: ms
parameters.description: An integer value from 0 to 999. If this argument is not supplied, its value is set to 0.

methods.description: Returns a new Date object holding the current date and time.
methods.longdesc: If parameters are supplied, returns a new Date object holding the supplied date and time.

methods.name: getDate
methods.description: Returns the day of the month of the specified Date object in local time.

methods.name: getDay
methods.description: Returns the day of the week for the specified Date object in local time.
methods.longdesc: This is an integer from 0 (Sunday) to 6 (Saturday).  Returns the day of the week for date.

methods.name: getYear
methods.description: Returns the year of the specified Date object, as a difference from 1900, in local time.

methods.name: getFullYear
methods.description: Returns the four digit year of the specified Date object in local time.

methods.name: getHours
methods.description: Returns the hour of the specified Date object in local time.

methods.name: getMilliseconds
methods.description: Returns the milliseconds of the specified Date object in local time.

methods.name: getMinutes
methods.description: Returns the minutes of the specified Date object in local time.

methods.name: getMonth
methods.description: Returns the month of the specified Date object in local time.

methods.name: getSeconds
methods.description: Returns the seconds of the specified Date object in local time.

methods.name: getTime
methods.description: Returns the number of milliseconds since midnight January 1,1970 UTC for the specified Date object.

methods.name: getTimezoneOffset
methods.description: Returns the difference in minutes between the computer's local time and UTC.

methods.name: getUTCDate
methods.description: Returns the day of the month of the specified Date object according to UTC.

methods.name: getUTCDay
methods.description: Returns the day of the week for the specified Date object according to UTC.

methods.name: getUTCFullYear
methods.description: Returns the four digit year of the specified Date object according to UTC.

methods.name: getUTCHours
methods.description: Returns the hour of the specified Date object according to UTC.

methods.name: getUTCMilliseconds
methods.description: Returns the milliseconds of the specified Date object according to UTC.

methods.name: getUTCMinutes
methods.description: Returns the minutes of the specified Date object according to UTC.

methods.name: getUTCMonth
methods.description: Returns the month of the specified Date object according to UTC.

methods.name: getUTCSeconds
methods.description: Returns the seconds of the specified Date object according to UTC.

methods.name: setDate

parameters.name: date
parameters.description: An integer from 1 to 31 indicating the day of the month.

methods.description: Sets the day of the month of a specified Date object according to local time.
methods.longdesc: Returns the number of milliseconds between the new date and midnight, January 1, 1970.

methods.name: setFullYear

parameters.name: year
parameters.description: A four-digit integer value indicating the year to set.

methods.description: Sets the year of a specified Date object according to local time.
methods.longdesc: This method can also set month and date if those arguments are specified. Returns the number of milliseconds between the new date and midnight, January 1, 1970.

methods.name: setHours

parameters.name: hour
parameters.description: An integer value from 0 (midnight) to 23 (11 PM).

methods.description: Sets the hours of a specified Date object according to local time.
methods.longdesc: Returns the number of milliseconds between the new date and midnight, January 1, 1970.

methods.name: setMilliseconds

parameters.name: ms
parameters.description: An integer value from 0 to 999.

methods.description: Sets the milliseconds of a specified Date object according to local time.
methods.longdesc: Returns the number of milliseconds between the new date and midnight, January 1, 1970.

methods.name: setMinutes

parameters.name: minutes
parameters.description: An integer value from 0 to 59.

methods.description: Sets the minutes of a specified Date object according to local time.
methods.longdesc: Returns the number of milliseconds between the new date and midnight, January 1, 1970.

methods.name: setSeconds

parameters.name: seconds
parameters.description: An integer value from 0 to 59.

methods.description: Sets the seconds of a specified Date object according to local time.
methods.longdesc: Returns the number of milliseconds between the new date and midnight, January 1, 1970.

methods.name: setMonth

parameters.name: month
parameters.description: An integer value from 0 (Jan) to 11 (Dec).

methods.description: Sets the month of a specified Date object according to local time.
methods.longdesc: Returns the number of milliseconds between the new date and midnight, January 1, 1970.

methods.name: setUTCDate

parameters.name: date
parameters.description: An integer from 1 to 31 indicating the day of the month.

methods.description: Sets the date of a specified Date object according to universal time.
methods.longdesc: Returns the number of milliseconds between the new date and midnight, January 1, 1970 in UTC time.

methods.name: setUTCFullYear

parameters.name: year
parameters.description: The year expressed in four digits.

methods.description: Sets the year of a specified Date object according to UTC, can also set the month and date.
methods.longdesc: Returns the number of milliseconds between the date set and midnight, January 1, 1970, in UTC.

methods.name: setUTCHours

parameters.name: hours
parameters.description: An integer value from 0 (midnight) to 23 (11 PM) indicating the hour to be set.

methods.description: Sets the hours of a specified Date object according to UTC.
methods.longdesc: Returns the number of milliseconds between the date set and midnight, January 1, 1970, in UTC.

methods.name: setUTCMilliseconds

parameters.name: ms
parameters.description: An integer value in the range of 0 to 999 indicating the number of milliseconds to set.

methods.description: Sets the milliseconds of a specified Date object according to UTC.
methods.longdesc: Returns the number of milliseconds between the date set and midnight, January 1, 1970, in UTC.

methods.name: setUTCMinutes

parameters.name: min
parameters.description: An integer value in the range 0 to 59 indicating the number of minutes to be set.

methods.description: Sets the minutes of a specified Date object according to UTC.
methods.longdesc: Returns the number of milliseconds between the date set and midnight, January 1, 1970, in UTC.

methods.name: setUTCSeconds

parameters.name: sec
parameters.description: An integer value in the range 0 to 59 indicating the number of seconds to set.

methods.description: Sets the seconds of a specified Date object according to UTC.
methods.longdesc: Returns the number of milliseconds between the date set and midnight, January 1, 1970, in UTC.

methods.name: setUTCMonth

parameters.name: month
parameters.description: An integer value in the range 0 (Jan.) to 11 (Dec.) indicating the month to set.

methods.description: Sets the month of a specified Date object according to UTC.
methods.longdesc: Returns the number of milliseconds between the date set and midnight, January 1, 1970, in UTC.

methods.name: setTime

parameters.name: ms
parameters.description: An integer indicating the number of milliseconds between the date set and midnight, January 1, 1970.

methods.description: Sets the date of a specified Date object in milliseconds since midnight, January 1, 1970.
methods.longdesc: Returns the value of ms.

methods.name: setYear

parameters.name: year
parameters.description: An integer value indicating the year to set.
parameters.longdesc: The method interprets a 1- or 2- digit value to mean the 1900s; for example, 13 is interpreted to mean 1913.

methods.description: Sets the year of a specified Date object according to local time, as a difference between the current year and 1900.
methods.longdesc: Returns the number of milliseconds between the date set and midnight, January 1, 1970.

methods.name: toDateString
methods.longdesc: Returns the date as a string.

methods.name: toTimeString
methods.longdesc: Returns the time as a string.

methods.name: toLocaleString
methods.longdesc: Returns a string value representing the date and time stored in the Date object in human readable format (localized).

methods.name: toLocaleDateString
methods.longdesc: Returns the date as a localized string.

methods.name: toLocaleTimeString
methods.longdesc: Returns the time as a localized string.

methods.name: toGMTString
methods.longdesc: Returns the date and time adjusted to GMT (UTC) as a string.

methods.name: toUTCString
methods.longdesc: Returns the date and time adjusted to UTC as a string.

methods.name: toString
methods.description: Returns a string value representing the date and time stored in the Date object in human readable format.
methods.longdesc: Returns the following string is an example of the format returned by this method: Mon Aug 13, 10:54:21 GMT-0700 2001.

methods.name: valueOf
methods.description: The valueOf() method returns the number of milliseconds that have passed since midnight, Returns an integer.

methods.name: toSource
methods.description: Creates a string representation of this object that can be fed back to eval() to re-create an object. Works only with built-in classes.
